SIMPLE: given
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Given
<hw>Giv"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <def><pos>p. p. & a.</pos> from
<er>Give</er>, <pos>v.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Math. & Logic)</fld> <def>Granted; assumed;
supposed to be known; set forth as a known quantity, relation, or
premise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Disposed; inclined; -- used with an <pos>adv.</pos>;
<as>as, virtuously <ex>given</ex></as>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Stated; fixed; <as>as, in a <ex>given</ex>
time</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Given name</b></col>, <cd>the Christian name, or name
<xex>given</xex> by one's parents or guardians, as distinguished from
the <contr>surname</contr>, which is inherited.</cd>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>givenness</ent>⟦br⟧
